contentrichtext.text: The word '''anser''' comes from Latin, meaning ''goose'', and can refer to: * [[Anser (genus)]], the genus of grey geese * The star [[Alpha Vulpeculae]], or ''Anser'', in the constellation Vulpecula * [[ACME Anser]], an amphibious jet fighter project of the 1950s * [[Sega Mega Anser]], a Sega Mega Drive accessory * [[Analytic Services]] (ANSER), a security and defense analysis group * [[Argonne/Northwestern_Solar_Energy_Research_Center]], a joint research program at Argonne National Lab and Northwestern University {{disambig}}
